==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Statical
<hw>Stat"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(-⟦icr⟧*k⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>statiko`s</grk> causing to stand, skilled in weighing, fr.
<grk>'ista`nai</grk> to cause to stand: cf. F. <ets>statique</ets>. See
<er>Stand</er>, and cf. <er>Stage</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Resting;
acting by mere weight without motion; <as>as, <ex>statical</ex>
pressure; <ex>static</ex> objects.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Pertaining to bodies at rest or in
equilibrium.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Static electricity</b></col>, <col><b>Statical
electricity</b></col></mcol>. <cd>See the Note under
<er>Electricity</er>, 1.</cd> -- <col><b>Statical moment</b></col>.
<cd>See under <er>Moment</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Statically</ent>⟦br⟧
